I just finished reading White Fragility for my anti-racism book club, and I thought it was very insightful (as well as a quick and relatively easy read). The book is written by a white woman as a resource for other white people. I have to admit, when I picked it up, I first thought that, as a progressive liberal, the book wasnâ€™t really intended for me. DiAngelo shattered that illusion immediately by stating that I am exactly the type of person this book was written for.

I learned a lot about how our history and privilege create certain reactions to racial discussions in white people and how we can begin to correct our behavior. DiAngelo spoke about racism in a way Iâ€™ve never heard before and, while I recognize there may be legitimate critiques about the author or the way she discusses the subject, this book felt important to my antiracist learning. I give it a 4.8/5.0. âœŠğŸ¿

